==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hypnocyst
<hw>Hyp"no*cyst</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ sleep +
E. <ets>cyst</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A cyst in which some
unicellular organisms temporarily inclose themselves, from which they
emerge unchanged, after a period of drought or deficiency of food. In
some instances, a process of spore formation seems to occur within such
cysts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypnogenic</ent>⟦br⟧
